claim.claim-text:
10. A method of purging ammonia-containing vapors for an engine, comprising:
storing an ammonia-containing fluid in a first storage device;
generating ammonia vapors in the first storage device and storing said generated ammonia vapors in a second storage device;
delivering said ammonia vapors upstream of an engine combustion chamber, including to the first storage device, during a first condition and into an engine exhaust upstream of an SCR catalyst during a second condition.
